net.sf.mmm.music.datatype.api

Enum MusicalKey

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<MusicalKey>
      • net.sf.mmm.music.datatype.api.MusicalKey
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<MusicalKey>

    public enum MusicalKey
extends Enum<MusicalKey>
    This enum represents a musical key. It represents a diatonic scale based on a fundamental tone (called tonika) and a tonal system.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)

      • getDiatonicScale

        public List<TonePitch> getDiatonicScale()

      • getChromaticScale

        public List<TonePitch> getChromaticScale()
        Returns:
        the List with twelve TonePitches of the chromatic scale for this MusicalKey starting from tonika.

      • getChromaticSignTones

        public List<TonePitch> getChromaticSignTones()
        Returns:
        the List with the tones for the chromatic signs of this MusicalKey. Will be empty for C_MAJOR or A_MINOR. Will contain only sharp or only flat tones. E.g. for D_MAJOR it will contain TonePitch.FIS and TonePitch.CIS and for C_MINOR it will contain TonePitch.B_FLAT, TonePitch.ES, TonePitch.AS.

      • getEnharmonicStyle

        public EnharmonicStyle getEnharmonicStyle()
        Returns:
        the EnharmonicStyle. EnharmonicStyle.NORMAL for C_MAJOR and A_MINOR. EnharmonicStyle.SHARP if the chromatic sign tones are sharp. EnharmonicStyle.FLAT if the chromatic sign tones are flat.

      • transposeChromatic

        public MusicalKey transposeChromatic(int semitoneSteps)
        Transposes this MusicalKey.
        Parameters:
        semitoneSteps - is the number of semitone steps to transpose. A positive value transposes towards a higher pitch, a negative value transposes towards a lower pitch. A value of zero (0) will have no change.
        Returns:
        the transposed MusicalKey.

      • getTone

        public TonePitch getTone(Interval interval)
        Returns the tone for the given Interval.
        Parameters:
        interval - is the Interval such as e.g. Solmization.MI, ChromaticInterval.MAJOR_THIRD, or DiatonicInterval.THIRD.
        Returns:
        the requested TonePitch of this MusicalKey.

        public static MusicalKey fromName(String value)
        This method gets the MusicalKey for the given value.
